      {
        "id": 4088274,
        "name": "Richard Albert",
        "username": "Richard_Albert",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/richard_albert/{size}/95072_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-06-07T03:10:15.736Z",
        "cooked": "<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/4X/2/8/c/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a\" title=\"20230531_124111\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/2/8/c/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a_2_281x500.jpeg\" alt=\"20230531_124111\" data-base62-sha1=\"5Ov8vrB7QuZ4HZmZEfJ2YWrdMGC\" width=\"281\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/2/8/c/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a_2_281x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/2/8/c/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a_2_421x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/2/8/c/28c051493ebbaa104ffccc9dc9839e8a148c011a_2_562x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"8D6960\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">20230531_124111</span><span class=\"informations\">1920\u00d73413 221 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div><br>\nThis is the second 1978 Sonoma County Pinot Noir from the Davis Cellar. Both were the first Pinot Noirs released by their respective wineries Dehlinger a few years ago for an anniversary and now Kalin for my birthday last week and in honor of Terry Leighton who recently passed. We lost a brilliant individual, super knowledgeable winemaker and former Chair of the Microbiology Dept at Berkeley. He and Francis stopped by the Marin Wine Cellar starting in the 80s delivering their wines, hanging out and were our wine dinner companions repeatedly. When I told him I had a 1978 in my cellar a five years ago, he was rather curious how I managed that rare find. He would have been proud of its showing which confirmed his expectations. Terry was known for not releasing his wines until he thought they were showing well, checkout the recent Kalin releases. RIP Terry.<br>\nThis bottle took about ten minutes to reveal its toned down, yet plentiful fruits, red cherry dominated with cranberry lurking. It offered sous-bois and distinct minerality, in a medium bodied format. The tannins remained in the background for more than an hour and a half.<br>\nI wrote about the Dehlinger previously with its in your face spice, cherry and sandalwood.<br>\n1978s rock! My respect for the vintage continues to grow for both Pinot Noirs(Chalone as well) and for some stellar Cabs still kickin.</p>",
