      {
        "id": 4088665,
        "name": "Richard Albert",
        "username": "Richard_Albert",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/richard_albert/{size}/95072_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-06-07T17:56:40.342Z",
        "cooked": "<p>William, I believe it was Terry\u2019s first Pinot Noir with just a Sonoma designation.<br>\nI was blown away as well by the color to the rim and with no color striations.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/4X/0/2/c/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779\" title=\"0929181709\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/0/2/c/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779_2_690x388.jpeg\" alt=\"0929181709\" data-base62-sha1=\"oQPoaYXIOcvxz4DNGN9VYcjDD3\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/0/2/c/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779_2_690x388.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/0/2/c/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779_2_1035x582.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/4X/0/2/c/02cf2d390d2e17dee98acda5cbca84f4f45d8779_2_1380x776.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"706C6B\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">0929181709</span><span class=\"informations\">1920\u00d71080 104 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div><br>\nHere is the amazing 1978 Dehlinger from five years ago, after being open for a couple of hours. Please pardon the  finger food stained glass, the color was  youthful as well. This was also a first release with a Sonoma designation.<br>\nI forgot to mention the intense rose petal on the nose as well.</p>",
